-- Bangladesh Police Arrest Opposition Members Ahead of Strike
-- B y   A r u n   D e v n a t h
-- 2013-11-09T04:57:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-09/bangladesh-police-arrest-opposition-members-ahead-of-strike.html
Bangladesh  police arrested at least
three senior members of the main opposition party that has
called for a nationwide strikes aimed at forcing the government
to resign.  Bangladesh Nationalist Party Standing Committee members
Moudud Ahmed, M.K. Anwar and Rafiqul Islam Miah were detained by
plainclothes police, Ruhul Kabir Rizvi, joint secretary general
of the BNP, said at a media briefing in Dhaka last night. The
party and its allies have announced a 72-hour shutdown starting
tomorrow to demand Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina step down and
appoint a caretaker government to oversee 2014 polls.  BNP Chairwoman Khaleda Ziaâ€™s adviser Abdul Awal Mintoo and
Special Assistant Shimul Biswas were also arrested today,
according to Bdnews24.com.  The ruling Awami League and the BNP are the biggest
political parties in Bangladesh, where elections are scheduled
to be held by Jan. 25.  To contact the reporter on this story:
